<br>
Firstly, I won't do it if I don't want to.  I've turned down people for ports who offered hundreds of plat.  Look, my time is my own, and in the end as someone said, it's the only currency any of us have that's really of any worth.  I'm going to spend it how I want, and help whom I want.<br>
<br>
Secondly, I'd rather have your gratitude than your money.  Giving someone closure by taking the donation may be &quot;polite,&quot; but I find I prefer to be remembered for my generosity, not as just another transaction you had to make in order to get what you wanted.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#581212><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ubhodiivv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bhodiivv</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(3/22/02 2:01:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poor</span><hr size=1> honestly the other night i was called apon by a guild because they had had a total wipe out in PoG.  Now being the kidder I am I walked in when the raid leaders where there and said 50pp a head.  now there were about 20+ people I did rez and being as it was I wasn't wasting mana cause of my epic I didn't plan to charge.  After I did rez everyone I was overed alot of money from the people.  However I did not accept.  I don't mind going somewhere if I get a port and an escort.  as long as I don't risk myself and am not busy I don't charge no matter if I have 100pp in the bank...(NORMAL tank I hang around is a loot hog...)  So as far as accepting donations or not.  Its your call.  Just remember if you don't do quest gear or have no drop gear you need money for spells in the future.   <p>Bhodi Li "Battle Child" Of Tunare.
