<center><i>Though they be only breath, words which I command are immortal.</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#581212><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukindolandxem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kindol and Xem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(3/23/02 8:08:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poor</span><hr size=1> I never ask for money or any reimbursment.  If I can Rez you if i'm not busy, I rez ya.  Some ask how much.  I usually tell them that I didn't rez for money and is not necessary.  Sometimes they put up money anyway.  Depending on my mood I will accept it or not.  People if they give, will give an amount that they feel is decent yet not take alot of their own money, if they don't have alot.  I dunno, jut my thoughts.<br>
