 <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=62530">Kindol</a> and <a target="new"href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=70535">Xemenz</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7A3412><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/udalcharis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalcharis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(3/24/02 1:49:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poor</span><hr size=1> I rez with my alt all the time.... it's not a huge deal usually... People tend to only give ya money if they can afford it it seems, most always say thanks.... although not always.... but I could have missed a few thank yous do to combat and trying to save someone's ass :P <p><img src="http://orderofhasson.com/members/dalcharis_sig1.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#581212><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ulaylalitebringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Layla Litebringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(4/14/02 7:41:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Poor</span><hr size=1> I don't really have absolutes for any rez situation.  Many times I'll accept donations if offered, doesn't matter the amount. I figure its all part of them wanting to say thank you. Could be a few gold pieces for all I care, it's the thought that counts. But the verbal thanks I get is where its really at for me. If its someone less than 40, and not an obvious twink, I'll try to politely refuse as I know what its like at that level.  When  I have my epic, I doubt I'll ever accept donations at all if I can avoid it.  What goes around comes around is my theory. Being treated with good manners and respect go a long way with me.<br>
<br>
I have had a few who want to give me more than was reasonable, and I have refused it.  But this is a fluid situation, as some do get annoyed if I refuse, and thats bad karma which I try to avoid. Gems, especially peridots, are never turned down.  Rezzing other clerics and chanters has always been free, as well as friends and guildmates.  <br>
<br>
Luckily I have a good friends who know me and help me with pp or peridots when needed.  As for Rathe Mountains, I made a nice sum for my spells when needed by pairing up with friends, usually a druid and/or a necro.  Necro and cleric combo can rule big time in RM, and if you have a tracker friend join you, its even easier to get all the pp you'd need in a couple days.<br>
<br>
I guess the only &quot;absolute&quot; method I try to play by is to do all I can to keep the good karma flowing in the game.  I have more fun that way and hope others do too.<br>
<br>
HUGS! <p>Layla Lightbringer<br>
Cleric of the 52nd Level<br>
<br>
<br>
<img border="0" src="http://www.ewebheads.com/graphics/EQ-sig.jpg" alt="Layla Litebringer, Bringer of Light and Life" width="400" height="60"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ulaylalitebringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Layla Litebringer</A> at: 4/14/02 7:43:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7A3412><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uvarba.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Varba</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(4/15/02 1:11:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Donations</span><hr size=1> I ushally say nothing when asked about rez fees.  If it is a group mate or guildie I absolutely refuse anything but future aid for quests or something.<br>
